00:00:01.160 --> 00:00:05.560
OK, so, as you know, I recently agreed to do a FAQ video,

00:00:05.880 --> 00:00:09.000
which means I answer some questions of Internet users.

00:00:09.000 --> 00:00:13.360
So, I don't know if it's such a good idea because we received more than 3000 questions

00:00:13.360 --> 00:00:20.920
and... it wasn't a lot of fun for Antoine who had to sort them.

00:00:20.920 --> 00:00:25.420
He put them in order and tried to link them to the appropriate documents,

00:00:25.420 --> 00:00:29.180
because we have a document that we open whenever you ask a precise question,

00:00:29.180 --> 00:00:34.080
it is "L'Avenir en commun" ("Common future"), our program, and later on, I will show you some booklets.

00:00:34.080 --> 00:00:38.180
So we looked for answers in the book ... We have to prepare this, don't we?

00:00:38.180 --> 00:00:43.580
I took the questions on top of the stack, OK? It's the only criterion, and now I'll try to answer your questions.

00:00:43.580 --> 00:00:46.720
I'll try to be quick, otherwise we'll be there forever and a day,

00:00:46.720 --> 00:00:51.860
and as you know, I like to explain things in details, but it's not a good idea for this kind of exercise.

00:00:51.860 --> 00:00:55.860
So... Depending on your reactions, I'll see what I'll need to improve,

00:00:55.860 --> 00:01:00.060
but I must say it's quite extraordinary to receive 3000 questions.

00:01:00.200 --> 00:01:06.920
It enables us to have a dialogue that is maybe more interesting than more formal discussions.

00:01:07.500 --> 00:01:13.300
So thank you for giving me this idea, really, because it is a thought-provoking exercise for my work.

00:01:13.300 --> 00:01:14.320
OK, let's begin!

00:01:14.440 --> 00:01:16.440
So Martin asks:

00:01:16.440 --> 00:01:21.460
"You said on many occasions that one of your first measures would be to establish a constituent assembly.

00:01:21.680 --> 00:01:24.900
How do you intend to initiate and organize this process?"

00:01:25.180 --> 00:01:30.160
So... First, it's in the program, and we consider that if people elect me, it means that they agree with this idea.

00:01:30.400 --> 00:01:36.640
And to me, this is a key idea because... It's important to understand that... What is it that makes a people?

00:01:36.880 --> 00:01:42.180
It's the fact that people decide laws together and obey the laws even when they don't agree with them.

00:01:42.460 --> 00:01:47.340
When I disagree with laws that I dont like, well I still disagree with them, but I obey them.

00:01:47.540 --> 00:01:53.120
So I struggle for their repeal, for modifications, and sometimes, I try to convince people not to vote for them,

00:01:53.120 --> 00:01:54.840
but I accept to obey them.

00:01:54.840 --> 00:02:01.000
So the rules of the game are very important, because they have a direct consequence:

00:02:01.000 --> 00:02:05.020
you relinquish your freedom, which means you give up the possibility of doing what you want,

00:02:05.140 --> 00:02:07.580
because you decide to obey the law.

00:02:07.820 --> 00:02:11.800
So... You could argue that when you don't obey the law, you are punished.

00:02:11.820 --> 00:02:16.480
OK, but obeying the law is also a personal principle.

00:02:16.520 --> 00:02:21.860
There are other rules you disagree with which you obey. 
So it is crucial.

00:02:22.000 --> 00:02:27.880
This was my first point. Now my second point is that a people builds itself... It becomes a people.

00:02:28.080 --> 00:02:32.700
It's not only because we have borders that we are French!

00:02:32.760 --> 00:02:36.620
We are French even beyond our borders, right? So what could it be?

00:02:36.620 --> 00:02:40.060
I already said it a hundred times! It is not a skin color, it is not a religion,

00:02:40.060 --> 00:02:42.780
because there are all the religions and skin colors in this country,

00:02:42.780 --> 00:02:49.860
etc etc. It's not even the french language, because it is an official language in 29 countries or so.

00:02:49.860 --> 00:02:55.280
It's really the law that we have in common 
and the rules that frame the making of laws that define us as a people.

00:02:55.280 --> 00:03:01.340
So the constituent assembly is the assembly that is convened to decide the rules of the game,

00:03:01.340 --> 00:03:07.700
and the rules of the game, it's the constitution. It organizes public authorities, guarantees civil liberties, etc etc.

00:03:07.700 --> 00:03:12.080
So it is a key aspect to me. Besides, it is the core of my revolutionary strategy.

00:03:12.080 --> 00:03:17.540
How should we proceed to transform society radically?

00:03:17.540 --> 00:03:22.720
There are several ways to do this. For instance, you could decide to use clubs and rifles to do this,

00:03:22.720 --> 00:03:27.080
or you could establish a dictatorship.

00:03:27.080 --> 00:03:32.240
But there's another method: voting, and getting citizens involved.

00:03:32.240 --> 00:03:35.980
But that's not the easiest part! How long do you think people will stay involved?

00:03:35.980 --> 00:03:39.160
"One day, two days, maybe three days, and then what? Not every day!"

00:03:39.160 --> 00:03:42.940
Well in a way, yes. We need to stay on the lookout, we need to stay well-informed.

00:03:42.940 --> 00:03:46.680
People are ready to do that. It's not the case anymore, but in the past,

00:03:46.680 --> 00:03:51.880
everybody watched the news on TV to get information. When there was a good documentary on TV, everyone watched it.

00:03:51.880 --> 00:03:55.520
Now people pick up information here and there, but they do it wisely

00:03:55.520 --> 00:03:58.500
They try to find documentation, to form an opinion on such and such issue.

00:03:58.500 --> 00:04:08.280
You see, there is an opportuny to act on public matters on the long term.

00:04:08.280 --> 00:04:14.360
To put it simply, the constitution has to create the people.

00:04:14.360 --> 00:04:17.840
You might say "Well the French people already exist!" Tatata! Don't be so sure!

00:04:17.840 --> 00:04:21.100
Of course they do, everyone has an ID, and we're French.

00:04:21.100 --> 00:04:26.100
But feeling that we are bound by a common future is not the same, we have to build this!

00:04:26.340 --> 00:04:30.160
We need this moment when we bind together as a people.

00:04:30.180 --> 00:04:36.720
We need to write a new constitution in order to define our relations toward one another and the rights we have.

00:04:36.900 --> 00:04:40.420
I already witnessed experiences of constituent assemblies in Latin America.

00:04:40.420 --> 00:04:44.160
They really were impressive because there were real debates.

00:04:44.260 --> 00:04:47.460
In Ecuador, they even changed the place of the assembly.

00:04:47.460 --> 00:04:51.220
Instead of setting the assembly in Quito, the equivalent of Paris, they chose another city.

00:04:51.220 --> 00:04:56.840
People went there. There were processions to present the demands of the people to the deputies of the constituent assembly,

00:04:56.920 --> 00:05:02.240
An office gathered these demands and tried to turn them into articles of the constitution,

00:05:02.240 --> 00:05:04.240
then people discussed them and voted.

00:05:04.240 --> 00:05:12.400
Also, when Venezuela changed its constitution, authorities printed articles of the constitution on rice and pasta bags

00:05:12.400 --> 00:05:16.120
in order to get people involved and have them discuss the articles at home. Isn't it a good idea?

00:05:16.120 --> 00:05:19.240
And all this had the effect of getting people involved and making them think.

00:05:19.240 --> 00:05:24.960
As for us, the current constitution of 1958 changed a lot,

00:05:24.960 --> 00:05:29.720
it really comes from another era! I mean... it was 1958!

00:05:29.720 --> 00:05:34.960
It was the end of colonial wars and... France was a very rural country.

00:05:34.960 --> 00:05:40.340
Now France is a completely urban country, and thankfully, colonial wars are over.

00:05:40.340 --> 00:05:43.980
We are involved in military interventions, but not in conflicts

00:05:43.980 --> 00:05:47.000
that involve the whole population as before.

00:05:47.000 --> 00:05:52.440
And above all, the population is much younger, much more mixed culturally, much more educated...

00:05:52.440 --> 00:05:57.620
Because the school system is often criticized, and some people really think that it's not worth a dime

00:05:57.740 --> 00:06:01.720
and that the French are just a bunch of illiterate and ignorant people, but that's not true!

00:06:01.720 --> 00:06:04.500
The education level is way higher everywhere,

00:06:04.580 --> 00:06:13.140
and waves of immigration transformed the French people, so much so that it is now a new people.

00:06:13.140 --> 00:06:15.000
It's a quick process, you know?

00:06:15.000 --> 00:06:19.760
For instance, few of my grandparents were French, but you can see that I am a fervent patriot.

00:06:19.760 --> 00:06:26.260
I'm saying all this to explain that a people writes a constitution in order to build itself.

00:06:26.400 --> 00:06:31.340
So how does a constituent assembly work? First, it's in the program, it's the first measure, so you can't miss it.

00:06:32.460 --> 00:06:36.580
If I become President, I'll use Article 11 of the current constitution

00:06:36.580 --> 00:06:42.080
in order to initiate a referendum on the establishment of a constituent assembly.

00:06:42.240 --> 00:06:47.800
That's the first part. Then once the French people voted yes, we'll establish the assembly.

00:06:48.120 --> 00:06:51.860
It is not the same as the National Assembly, it is a different assembly,

00:06:52.700 --> 00:06:55.780
and there will be rules to choose the deputies of this assembly.

00:06:55.780 --> 00:07:01.340
First, you will not be able to become a member of the constituent assembly if you have already been a member of a previous assembly.

00:07:01.520 --> 00:07:04.560
Why is that? Not because I want to accuse those who have already been elected.

00:07:04.660 --> 00:07:10.680
We just want a fresh look on the future constitution, with people who never got involved in public affairs,

00:07:10.820 --> 00:07:15.780
people who think. They will have their own background of course, but it will be new for them,

00:07:15.780 --> 00:07:19.940
they'll examine the situation and say: "Well here's what we should do in a normal country",

00:07:19.940 --> 00:07:23.120
and not: "Well, that's the way I was elected the last time".

00:07:23.120 --> 00:07:25.760
OK, so you understood what I said.

00:07:25.960 --> 00:07:30.460
So one part of the assembly has to be elected, and I propose to draw lots to choose the rest of the assembly.

00:07:30.620 --> 00:07:34.260
This leads me to another question. Someone asked:

00:07:34.540 --> 00:07:37.040
So his pseudonym is "That's so nuclear"...

00:07:37.980 --> 00:07:41.240
I just can't get used to these pseudonyms... Anyway!

00:07:41.240 --> 00:07:45.000
So "That's so nuclear", "@slowbrain" (pun with "kite")...

00:07:45.000 --> 00:07:47.000
OK... "@slowbrain"

00:07:47.000 --> 00:07:50.640
"What is your opinion on drawing lots, that remains the most democratic way of selecting people?"

00:07:50.840 --> 00:07:54.140
Well no, it's not THE most democratic mean. That's not true.

00:07:54.140 --> 00:07:56.300
It's a democratic mean among others.

00:07:56.540 --> 00:08:02.780
When you draw lots, you hope that you will statistically obtain a fair representation

00:08:02.960 --> 00:08:06.320
of all the points of views in society. I understand this idea.

00:08:06.320 --> 00:08:12.820
By the way, when we established the first representative assembly of "La France Insoumise" in Lille,

00:08:12.820 --> 00:08:17.800
we drew lots to choose 2/3 of the members, so I'm not afraid of this method.

00:08:17.800 --> 00:08:24.220
But these 2/3 did at least agree with one idea: the candidate for the election, me.

00:08:24.720 --> 00:08:28.600
There has to be a minimum of consent to draw lots.

00:08:28.600 --> 00:08:31.560
So we'll draw lots to choose some members, and the rest will be elected. Why is that?

00:08:31.560 --> 00:08:35.380
Well it's because some problems cannot be solved by drawing lots.

00:08:35.380 --> 00:08:39.120
There has to be people who express and defend their opinion,

00:08:39.120 --> 00:08:45.040
and then people say: "Yes, well, he said that, the other guy said that,  and this woman defends another thesis..."

00:08:45.040 --> 00:08:49.760
We give it some thinking! And then the people we chose by drawing lots show their good faith,

00:08:49.760 --> 00:08:53.460
they think, they hear contradictory opinions and settle the matter.

00:08:53.760 --> 00:08:58.540
So if we want to make a choice between different opinions, we have to elect some of the members of the assembly.

00:08:58.540 --> 00:09:03.700
To take the example of the constitution, some people advocate a parliamentary system.

00:09:04.120 --> 00:09:07.760
All right? It means that the Parliament has the final say under any circumstances, it organizes everything.

00:09:07.960 --> 00:09:10.420
Other people advocate a presidential system.

00:09:10.660 --> 00:09:13.640
They think the President should have extensive powers,

00:09:13.720 --> 00:09:16.680
although he has to be under the control of the assembly.

00:09:16.680 --> 00:09:20.060
And there are people who think it has to be an in-between solution.

00:09:20.960 --> 00:09:23.940
For instance, the President could have extensive powers

00:09:23.940 --> 00:09:26.020
but he could be removed from office at any moment

00:09:26.180 --> 00:09:30.680
and the assembly could show it disapproves of his action or whatnot.

00:09:31.080 --> 00:09:33.320
We need to discuss all this, don't we ?

00:09:33.680 --> 00:09:37.020
And to tell you the truth, I advocate a parliamentary system,

00:09:37.020 --> 00:09:39.440
but sometimes, I think: "Well, I should listen to  other people's opinions".

00:09:39.440 --> 00:09:40.200
Anyway,!

00:09:40.980 --> 00:09:43.040
This is the reason why we will not only draw lots.

00:09:43.040 --> 00:09:46.180
We need to elect representatives and to choose representative by drawing lots.

00:09:46.560 --> 00:09:49.960
Of course, the most important aspect is the gender parity in the assembly,

00:09:49.960 --> 00:09:51.960
there has to be as many women as there are men,

00:09:51.960 --> 00:09:55.140
and in this, drawing lots is very useful.

00:09:55.520 --> 00:09:59.480
It will enable us to have a fair representation of the social diversity of the country.

00:09:59.480 --> 00:10:06.200
Without it, you will get the same people who already had the courage to stand as candidates.

00:10:06.200 --> 00:10:07.540
I know that!

00:10:07.540 --> 00:10:09.380
I come from this system, so I know what we're dealing with.

00:10:09.540 --> 00:10:13.600
So you're right to insist on the fact that we need to draw lots.

00:10:13.820 --> 00:10:17.760
Now "Mehdi la Suède" - why not - says:

00:10:18.540 --> 00:10:20.840
"How should the process of the constituent assembly take place?"

00:10:20.840 --> 00:10:25.340
Well, I just explained this process: first, a referendum, we convene an assembly,

00:10:25.380 --> 00:10:30.060
we make elections, we draw lots, and this assembly doesn't meet in the National Assembly but somewhere else.

00:10:30.060 --> 00:10:31.440
Someone else says:

00:10:31.440 --> 00:10:35.800
"How do you intend to implement your program if you leave office right after a constituent assembly was established?"

00:10:36.040 --> 00:10:38.920
I never said I would resign - Mehdi Hussain said that.

00:10:39.620 --> 00:10:43.260
When I become President, I will be elected within the framework of the 5th Republic,

00:10:43.260 --> 00:10:47.640
and I'll use an article from the constitution of the 5th Republic to convene the constituent assembly

00:10:47.900 --> 00:10:51.020
that will meet and work, and while it does that,

00:10:51.020 --> 00:10:53.740
while it writes a new constiution, I'll be the President.

00:10:54.020 --> 00:11:02.200
And I hope that there will be a majority of "La France Insoumise" deputies in the National Assembly

00:11:02.200 --> 00:11:04.580
to support the government's decisions.

00:11:04.700 --> 00:11:08.800
that I will appoint in accordance with the constitution of the 5th Republic.

00:11:08.800 --> 00:11:11.380
Thus, we'll get started right away, as soon as we take office,

00:11:11.380 --> 00:11:13.020
a lot of measures will be ready.

00:11:13.480 --> 00:11:16.780
And then when the constituent assembly finishes its work,

00:11:16.780 --> 00:11:19.620
the text will be presented to the French people,

00:11:19.680 --> 00:11:22.020
the French people vote yes, then this text immediately comes into effect,

00:11:22.020 --> 00:11:24.660
and I will no longer be President so that the new institutions may come into effect.

00:11:24.660 --> 00:11:26.360
I won't spin a yarn, you know.

00:11:26.440 --> 00:11:28.920
I'm not going to tell you: "You just wrote a new constitution that does not apply to me".

00:11:28.920 --> 00:11:30.920
Of course it will apply to me!

00:11:30.920 --> 00:11:34.860
So if the French people vote yes, then this constitution will apply to me and I'll leave office.

00:11:35.020 --> 00:11:39.720
Maybe I'll stand as a candidate again, but I don't think so.

00:11:39.720 --> 00:11:40.840
Anyway, that's the way it'll happen.

00:11:40.840 --> 00:11:45.000
There won't be any break and I won't leave office a week after I'm elected

00:11:45.000 --> 00:11:46.880
and say goodbye while you'll have to start from scratch.

00:11:46.880 --> 00:11:52.680
That's not the way it'll happen! I will implement the policies from my program as long as I'll be in office

00:11:52.680 --> 00:11:54.840
because the French people will have decided that.

00:11:55.100 --> 00:11:59.200
But I'll have a say in this constituent assembly.

00:11:59.220 --> 00:12:01.460
The difficulty is that I cannot say:

00:12:01.460 --> 00:12:04.320
"I propose to elect a constituent assembly

00:12:04.320 --> 00:12:07.500
but I, Jean-Luc Mélenchon, I'm going to tell you what the constitution will be".

00:12:07.700 --> 00:12:13.000
Some people want to do that. They say they'll propose a constitution, and there will be a vote on this text.

00:12:13.000 --> 00:12:15.000
This was General De Gaulle's method,

00:12:15.000 --> 00:12:17.700
but that's not our method, we don't intend to organize a plebiscite!

00:12:17.700 --> 00:12:22.000
There has to be a debate, people have to fight for their opinions,

00:12:22.340 --> 00:12:26.440
they have to argue and make their own opinion.

00:12:26.440 --> 00:12:30.820
We should not be afraid of debating, of having contradictory opinions.

00:12:30.820 --> 00:12:32.820
Sometimes, the debate heats up, so what?

00:12:32.820 --> 00:12:34.820
It gets cooler after a while, we're not savages, are we?

00:12:34.820 --> 00:12:38.020
As for me, I'll make propositions during the constituent process,

00:12:38.020 --> 00:12:40.560
but I won't tell you what you have to put in the constitution.

00:12:40.800 --> 00:12:44.800
One of my propositions concerns the guarantee of civil liberties,

00:12:44.800 --> 00:12:46.580
like the right to abortion ,

00:12:47.040 --> 00:12:51.300
or the right to die with dignity and to decide when we want to die.

00:12:51.300 --> 00:12:54.840
This means that you are the owner of your body and of your conscience.

00:12:54.840 --> 00:12:56.840
Do you hear me folks? Your body!

00:12:56.840 --> 00:13:02.440
You are the only owner of your body. It doesn't belong to other people, to your family, your husband or your children.

00:13:02.440 --> 00:13:03.860
It belongs to you.

00:13:03.860 --> 00:13:07.400
It's very important, it is the supreme civil liberty.

00:13:07.740 --> 00:13:12.060
And this goes for the right to abortion and for assisted suicide.

00:13:12.320 --> 00:13:14.980
But you know, as things go quickly, I'd rather be clear.

00:13:14.980 --> 00:13:19.120
I never said that I advocated abortion, I advocate the right to abortion. It's not the same thing!

00:13:19.320 --> 00:13:24.200
I know the problem of abortion doesn't arises differently for everyone,

00:13:24.200 --> 00:13:27.940
depending on your life, on your personality or on the context etc.

00:13:28.140 --> 00:13:32.340
Likewise, when I say that I advocate assisted suicide, it doesn't mean that I want you to commit suicide,

00:13:32.580 --> 00:13:35.180
or that I want to commit suicide, that's not the issue here!

00:13:35.580 --> 00:13:37.860
I'm saying this because people always exaggerate my ideas.

00:13:37.860 --> 00:13:42.540
No sooner did I finish a sentence that someone says something that makes a debate impossible.

00:13:42.540 --> 00:13:46.940
So I spoke about these fundamental liberties, but I have a third proposition, it is the green rule,

00:13:46.940 --> 00:13:52.160
which consists in forbidding to exploit the resources of the earth more than it can regenerate them.

00:13:52.160 --> 00:13:56.180
It would compel us to come up with good ideas to change our ways of producing.

00:13:56.500 --> 00:14:02.500
There's also another idea that I find very important, it is the right to dismiss elected representatives.

00:14:02.500 --> 00:14:05.500
And I mean every representatives. We should be able to dismiss them.

00:14:05.760 --> 00:14:08.380
To do that, we would use the method of the recall referendum.

00:14:08.520 --> 00:14:13.040
A number of citizens who say: "No, this guy can't remain in office any longer!"

00:14:13.040 --> 00:14:18.800
That guy is even worse! Just look at what he did! He lied to us, he betrayed and fooled us".

00:14:18.980 --> 00:14:21.820
I'm not accusing anyone, you can find them by yourselves.

00:14:22.260 --> 00:14:27.120
OK, so a recall referendum consists in gathering a number of signatures, a million for instance,

00:14:27.120 --> 00:14:30.120
or maybe two, to overthrow the President of the Republic,

00:14:30.460 --> 00:14:33.200
50,000 for a regional councillor... You got the point, right?

00:14:33.200 --> 00:14:37.720
And when you have enough signatures and signatories' polling card number,

00:14:37.720 --> 00:14:43.100
well we can organize a referendum: should he stay or should he go? That's it!

00:14:43.300 --> 00:14:48.020
Some people told me: "But people are are going to vote everyday!" Well, no, people aren't so stupid.

00:14:48.020 --> 00:14:51.800
First, you won't find one or two million signature just like that!

00:14:51.800 --> 00:14:56.740
You see? People should stop giving extreme examples to prevent ideas from progressing.

00:14:57.020 --> 00:15:01.360
It enables the people to have an eye on their representatives all the time,

00:15:01.480 --> 00:15:03.940
but it also gives stability to institutions.

00:15:04.140 --> 00:15:07.560
Because don't tell me that we'll run a great country like France

00:15:07.560 --> 00:15:10.880
with the system of the permanent general assembly, because I'm not buying it, it's not possible.

00:15:10.880 --> 00:15:13.040
How long should it take to establish a constituent assembly?"

00:15:13.200 --> 00:15:17.820
We'll do it quickly! we just need the time to establish the new assembly.

00:15:18.000 --> 00:15:25.800
There's a six-week period between the first round of the presidential election and the first round of the parliamentary elections,

00:15:26.060 --> 00:15:28.820
four weeks if we start counting from the second round.

00:15:28.820 --> 00:15:33.940
After that, we have to take office and then have the National Assembly vote the organization of a constituent assembly,

00:15:34.240 --> 00:15:41.000
so around September 2017, we'll be able to organize the election of the constituent assembly.

00:15:41.180 --> 00:15:44.140
