00:15:44.140 --> 00:15:46.880
@Luccio asks me: "Where does your swag come from?"

00:15:48.120 --> 00:15:49.300
Well...

00:15:49.300 --> 00:15:51.960
It's natural, that's why.

00:15:51.960 --> 00:15:56.900
@Christophe Geoffroy: "Conferences, public meetings, visits, interviews, videos, written articles...

00:15:56.900 --> 00:15:58.640
Where does your energy come from?"

00:15:58.640 --> 00:16:01.280
I don't know... I really don't.

00:16:02.900 --> 00:16:06.800
But let me tell you that when I relax...

00:16:07.660 --> 00:16:11.660
I can sleep for 12 or 13 hours, you should know that.

00:16:11.660 --> 00:16:15.580
But I haven't done that for a very long time.

00:16:15.840 --> 00:16:23.000
I think that when you do things passionately, and when people react positively...

00:16:23.040 --> 00:16:27.660
I mean I have to tell it like it is, when I talk to people, they react positively,

00:16:27.920 --> 00:16:32.600
they're kind and friendly for the most part.

00:16:33.100 --> 00:16:38.500
I don't know if there are many countries in which a candidate to a presidential election

00:16:38.500 --> 00:16:42.300
that comes third or fourth in the polls - I come third right now -

00:16:42.300 --> 00:16:47.400
can take the metro alone without being accompanied by bodyguards. Is there a country where it is possible? Well in France it is!

00:16:47.400 --> 00:16:49.000
And yet it is the country of moaners!

00:16:49.000 --> 00:16:51.440
The French are always described as a bunch of savages abroad.

00:16:51.640 --> 00:16:55.840
When you hear what the English say about us, you'd think our country is a jungle.

00:16:56.140 --> 00:17:00.320
Well, yes, it is a jungle, there are all sorts of cool ways of life here.

00:17:00.480 --> 00:17:05.520
Of course, we are just the way we are in this country,

00:17:05.520 --> 00:17:10.700
but for the most part, people are rather kind and pleasant, those I see in the subway at least.

00:17:10.700 --> 00:17:13.720
Maybe people who don't take the subway are unpleasant.

00:17:14.380 --> 00:17:18.200
For instance, when I walk in the street, I see people honking like lunatics for no reason.

00:17:18.200 --> 00:17:20.660
But people in the subway don't do that, and everything goes fine.

00:17:20.660 --> 00:17:23.900
@ET.G: "Did you read the manga comic 'Jean-Luc Mélenchon No Revolution', and what do you think of it?"

00:17:23.900 --> 00:17:25.900
Yes, I did.

00:17:25.900 --> 00:17:29.480
It didn't take much time to read it, because there are balloons.

00:17:29.680 --> 00:17:32.460
In French, they are called "phylactères".

00:17:32.880 --> 00:17:36.320
I liked the author's drawings and the offbeat aspect of this comic.

00:17:36.320 --> 00:17:38.860
Besides it's an honor. It's not everyone that has a manga comic about them!

00:17:38.860 --> 00:17:41.680
In the story, I ruthlessly fight my enemies, it's in my nature.

00:17:41.680 --> 00:17:44.940
The author perfectly understood how determined I am.

00:17:44.940 --> 00:17:49.660
I am grateful to David Chabant, I am very flattered that he wrote a manga comic about me,

00:17:50.040 --> 00:17:55.500
and I'm mad at my staff because they stole the only copy I had from me.

00:17:56.080 --> 00:18:02.820
I lost the only copy I had, and the author still hasn't sent me the comic with his inscription on it,

00:18:02.820 --> 00:18:04.840
I hope he'll get the message.

00:18:04.840 --> 00:18:09.820
Also, I'd be really happy if he offered me a strip. I would have it framed

00:18:09.820 --> 00:18:12.340
and I would put it at home, in my living room maybe.

00:18:12.640 --> 00:18:15.940
I mean, there aren't so many people who have a comic about them.

00:18:15.940 --> 00:18:17.660
"Do you intend to impose the use of Quinoa..."

00:18:17.660 --> 00:18:19.040
Honestly, @Teddy Bear...

00:18:20.060 --> 00:18:22.420
Was that question that necessary?

00:18:22.720 --> 00:18:26.400
"Do you intend to impose the use of quinoa in school canteens if by the greatest of miracles you happened to..."

00:18:26.400 --> 00:18:29.000
I do feel like the question is critical! Let me resume.

00:18:29.000 --> 00:18:32.400
"Do you intend to impose the use of quinoa in school canteens if by the greatest of miracles you happened to be elected?"

00:18:32.400 --> 00:18:36.200
First, it wouldn't be a miracle if I was elected, it would be the result of an election,

00:18:36.200 --> 00:18:38.580
and let me tell you that an election isn't a miracle.

00:18:38.900 --> 00:18:41.800
Besides, would it be the greatest of miracles? No, it would not.

00:18:41.800 --> 00:18:45.840
There are even greater miracles like walking on water, but I'm not capable of that.

00:18:45.840 --> 00:18:49.060
Apparently, very few people had the power to do that in the course of history.

00:18:49.260 --> 00:18:51.820
Do I intend to impose the use of quinoa?

00:18:51.820 --> 00:18:56.200
Let's suppose that I answered yes. I can see the headlines already: "Mélenchon wants to impose the use of quinoa!"

00:18:56.200 --> 00:19:03.180
I talked about quinoa because I want people to understand that we have to stop consuming meat proteines.

00:19:03.180 --> 00:19:06.720
Suppose I said: "We have to stop using meat proteins!"

00:19:06.720 --> 00:19:10.940
I would then give you statistics, but people would get bored and say "Next!"

00:19:10.940 --> 00:19:12.920
Of course you would!

00:19:12.920 --> 00:19:15.880
Especially if I added that we have to use vegetable proteins only.

00:19:16.060 --> 00:19:20.040
Your head would swell and you just could not stand it any longer.

00:19:20.040 --> 00:19:24.460
So I talked about quinoa, I showed the way I cook it, and I said that we couldn't continue to use meat proteins.

00:19:24.460 --> 00:19:30.480
And it worked well, because right after the interview, a pack of journalists started dressing me down

00:19:30.480 --> 00:19:33.060
barking: "Look! Mélenchon became a vegetarian!"

00:19:33.060 --> 00:19:38.200
but I'm not a vegetarian, I just try to eat as little meat proteins as possible.

00:19:38.200 --> 00:19:41.160
What matters is that it makes people think: "The guy is right!

00:19:41.160 --> 00:19:43.600
We don't want to keep eating all this meat

00:19:43.600 --> 00:19:46.200
at the expense of animals that go through atrocious suffering.

00:19:46.200 --> 00:19:51.500
Besides, it's not healthy, and the meat quality is poor because it is knacker's meat.

00:19:51.700 --> 00:19:56.280
Got it? So I won't impose the use of quinoa, but I'll force you to think about it.

00:19:56.420 --> 00:20:04.580
As for school canteens, it is true that we will impose 100% organic food on them.

00:20:04.720 --> 00:20:07.460
We need to use 100% organic food from local productions.

00:20:07.460 --> 00:20:12.640
How come you just can't find anyone that grows carrots for 150 miles around

00:20:12.640 --> 00:20:18.600
wherever you may be in the country! Did you know that?

00:20:18.920 --> 00:20:20.560
Well inform yourselves about carrots and you'll see.

00:20:20.560 --> 00:20:22.160
"Cannabis legalization"

00:20:22.160 --> 00:20:24.760
"@Lord nal... nagalfar"

00:20:26.940 --> 00:20:28.740
Lord! How humble!

00:20:29.240 --> 00:20:32.140
"Considering the good results obtained by the countries in which it was implemented,

00:20:32.140 --> 00:20:35.720
what is your opinion on cannabis legalization, in all its aspects?"

00:20:36.280 --> 00:20:40.960
Yes, you mean smoking joints and not just the medical use?

00:20:41.180 --> 00:20:45.620
That's what you mean, right? You're just afraid to put it like this, am I wrong, Lord Nagalfar?

00:20:45.620 --> 00:20:47.700
Come on! Don't be such a chicken!

00:20:48.160 --> 00:20:55.460
Now, the next question is from "@Mokritzy"... No! "@MokritZKy"!

00:20:56.300 --> 00:20:59.040
"A lot of people" - don't be so sure! -

00:20:59.040 --> 00:21:01.000
"wonder if we should we legalize it or not? And why?"

00:21:01.000 --> 00:21:01.540
OK!

00:21:01.640 --> 00:21:02.660
"@Miyajacky":

00:21:02.860 --> 00:21:08.560
Hello, and thank you. Do you think cannabis legalization could be economically and socially beneficial to France?"

00:21:08.640 --> 00:21:14.400
First, I don't care if it's good on the social and economic level.

00:21:14.480 --> 00:21:19.680
What matters is to deal with the use of cannabis as a public health problem.

00:21:19.860 --> 00:21:24.340
I am not in favor of the use of cannabis, but I am in favor of its legalization

00:21:24.340 --> 00:21:27.280
because I am against the use of cannabis. That's my first point.

00:21:28.440 --> 00:21:32.240
When a substance is forbidden, it is not possible to campaign against it.

00:21:32.240 --> 00:21:37.100
It is logic. By the way, you see all sorts of horrific campaigns against the use of tobacco,

00:21:37.180 --> 00:21:43.780
but you never see campaigns that say: "Look pals, if you smoke too much marijuana bla bla,

00:21:43.780 --> 00:21:46.120
it's going to ruin your health". Because it does!

00:21:46.400 --> 00:21:51.700
I'm talking about the recreational use of marijuana, not about other types uses

00:21:51.700 --> 00:21:54.400
like therapeutic, psychologic uses or whatnot.

00:21:54.760 --> 00:22:01.240
So, to me, it is important that we be able to campaign against the use of marijuana,

00:22:01.240 --> 00:22:03.420
but to do that, we have to legalize it.

00:22:04.080 --> 00:22:05.420
It's as simple as that!

00:22:05.460 --> 00:22:08.340
If you want to make prevention campaigns, then you have to legalize it!

00:22:08.540 --> 00:22:14.020
If you don't, if you're satisfied with today's terrific situation...

00:22:14.420 --> 00:22:20.400
People have to find all sorts of ways to hide a few grams!

00:22:20.400 --> 00:22:24.820
If you happen to be arrested with a few grams of hashish,

00:22:24.820 --> 00:22:27.320
then it's the end of the world and you're immediately sent to the police station.

00:22:27.400 --> 00:22:30.900
And if in addition to that you are caught sticking posters

00:22:30.900 --> 00:22:34.320
or making unpleasant graffitis on the walls, well your punishment is even more severe,

00:22:34.400 --> 00:22:36.540
because you are considered a suspicious person!

00:22:36.540 --> 00:22:38.540
I mean, let's be serious!

00:22:38.540 --> 00:22:42.160
This trade forms the basis for huge traffics,

00:22:43.080 --> 00:22:46.360
and it is a waste of time for policemen,

00:22:46.360 --> 00:22:50.160
it is a waste of time for judges, who could use this time for other objectives.

00:22:50.260 --> 00:22:59.720
This explains why you'll be satisfied if you're in favor of legalization, but also disappointed,

00:22:59.720 --> 00:23:03.380
I am absolutely opposed to the use of marijuana, which is why I want to legalize it.

00:23:03.560 --> 00:23:05.780
And don't call me a hypocrit!

00:23:05.940 --> 00:23:10.040
The hypocrisy is the ban on cannabis, when everyone knows that the use of marijuana is widely spread.

00:23:10.040 --> 00:23:12.540
People smoke it everywhere, and there's no way to stop it!

00:23:12.720 --> 00:23:17.800
I will be called a hypocrit because my way of fighting it is legalization,

00:23:17.980 --> 00:23:23.400
but no one says how hypocritical it is when there's a marijuana traffic on your block and that...

00:23:23.400 --> 00:23:26.660
What do you do in this case, pal? Do you call the police to make it stop the traffic?

00:23:26.660 --> 00:23:28.780
No, you don't! You even buy some!

00:23:28.860 --> 00:23:33.580
So enough! Enough with hypocrisy! It is a waste of time and a waste of money!

00:23:33.780 --> 00:23:38.080
It ruins people's health! We have to get down to business now!

00:23:38.140 --> 00:23:41.880
I hope my answer will initiate a debate.

00:23:42.180 --> 00:23:46.680
To tell you the truth, I must admit it took me some time to come to this conclusion.

00:23:47.160 --> 00:23:52.720
I used to think that legalizing the use of marijuana amounted to encouraging it.

00:23:52.980 --> 00:23:54.120
Now you know.

00:23:54.120 --> 00:23:58.560
And some of my friends came to tell me: "Don't do that! You're crazy!"

00:23:59.180 --> 00:24:01.700
But on the contrary, I think that I'd be crazy to say we should carry on like that.

00:24:01.820 --> 00:24:04.400
Let me explain how I came to this conclusion.

00:24:04.400 --> 00:24:10.200
I read some articles with different points of view about this issue, but not only French articles.

00:24:10.200 --> 00:24:15.280
I read articles from different countries, experiences in different countries, and they convinced me.

00:24:15.460 --> 00:24:19.000
Of course, I'm ready to hear contrary opinions, but since you asked my opinion, I give it to you.

00:24:19.000 --> 00:24:23.620
Now "@JesuisSousCôté" says:

00:24:23.620 --> 00:24:27.680
"What made you want to make videos on Youtube? Do you work on your own?"

00:24:28.020 --> 00:24:30.900
Well it's quite pathetic actually.

00:24:31.120 --> 00:24:36.300
At first, I was tired. I did not have time, often.

00:24:36.300 --> 00:24:39.840
I mean I was under pressure. I write articles on my blog every week.

00:24:39.840 --> 00:24:44.160
So the whole planet laughs at me because I probably write the longest blog articles in the world.

00:24:44.580 --> 00:24:47.900
They're about 30,000 characters long when they're concise,

00:24:47.980 --> 00:24:49.980
and 40,000 characters long the rest of the time!

00:24:49.980 --> 00:24:54.700
I basically write the equivalent of a book every two months!

00:24:54.960 --> 00:24:57.960
My articles amount to a book.

00:24:58.340 --> 00:25:04.160
So I feel stressed when I did everything I had to, because I know I have to get behind my keyboard

00:25:04.300 --> 00:25:09.260
for two hours or more. It takes a lot of time!

00:25:09.700 --> 00:25:13.700
Besides, my staff gives me notes, drafts sometimes, but mostly notes,

00:25:13.700 --> 00:25:16.160
and then I do a synthesis, and I keep it in mind as I write.

00:25:16.160 --> 00:25:20.960
So I decided we would do things differently. I set a camera on my desk

00:25:20.960 --> 00:25:24.600
and I thought I would record all that on my computer.

00:25:24.800 --> 00:25:27.540
To be honest, this was not reasonable, so I stopped.

00:25:27.760 --> 00:25:31.880
I therefore asked Antoine Nicolas for help. He works with me on these issues.

00:25:32.060 --> 00:25:37.720
He tried to make me understand nicely that I just could not do it, and that it would not be good if I did that on my own.

00:25:37.920 --> 00:25:42.620
I did one or two videos behind my computer, but I got it now, it's over!

00:25:42.780 --> 00:25:47.020
Besides, I had to show my appartment, and it always took me 2 hours to find the proper angle!

00:25:47.040 --> 00:25:50.000
It was really bad, so we decided to do as we do now.

00:25:50.200 --> 00:25:55.760
So we got started! I told Antoine: "Look, let's get down to business, I need to do a weekly review".

00:25:55.800 --> 00:26:00.480
So that's the way it started! We weren't really prepared. I just prepared my topics, read my notes,

00:26:00.480 --> 00:26:03.900
and poof, we got to work! And now I'm used to it!

00:26:03.900 --> 00:26:09.540
Speaking is not the hardest part for me, it's easier than writing.

00:26:09.780 --> 00:26:12.700
That's the way we had the idea, and then I...

00:26:12.840 --> 00:26:17.600
In the beginning, I watched some Youtubers' videos, and I liked it.

00:26:17.840 --> 00:26:23.660
I don't want to make people jealous, so I won't say who, but I did, and some of them were really funny.

00:26:24.040 --> 00:26:28.180
So I got started, and besides, some of my friends started to do the same.

00:26:28.520 --> 00:26:35.600
So I had a look at the work of my relatives, like Danielle Simonnet's videos for instance.

00:26:37.060 --> 00:26:38.880
I was really impressed!

00:26:39.160 --> 00:26:43.900
I liked it, and besides, I felt freer in the way I worked. So that's how I got the idea!

00:26:43.900 --> 00:26:47.200
Do I work on my own? No, I don't. There's Antoine Nicolas...

00:26:47.200 --> 00:26:53.720
and other friends, but I did not ask them if they wanted me to give their names, so I won't say who they are.

00:26:53.720 --> 00:26:57.960
There's the guy behind the camera for instance. I won't say his name, but he's there.

00:26:57.960 --> 00:27:03.960
We are... Two persons help me.

00:27:03.960 --> 00:27:09.120
After we filmed, they spend hours editing the videos. The videos look like there aren't any interruptions, but that's not the case actually.

00:27:09.120 --> 00:27:15.940
I need to stop to drink, to answer the phone when my damn phone won't stop ringing,

00:27:15.940 --> 00:27:18.800
which makes me think something serious happened. You know what I mean!

00:27:18.800 --> 00:27:22.620
This was my answer, dear @JesuisSousCôté!

00:27:23.040 --> 00:27:24.960
Now @Bridd asks:

00:27:24.960 --> 00:27:27.920
"What made ya wanna be a Youtuber?"

00:27:29.780 --> 00:27:31.400
I just answered the question!

00:27:31.680 --> 00:27:34.440
I thought it was easy, but I was wrong!

00:27:34.800 --> 00:27:36.920
Being a Youtuber is complicated.

00:27:36.920 --> 00:27:42.200
I'm saying this for those who think you just need to sit and talk to your camera for hours.

00:27:42.200 --> 00:27:46.160
There's preparation, there's work while we film,

00:27:46.160 --> 00:27:51.260
and there's work after that, because we have to edit the videos. It's a lot of work!

00:27:51.620 --> 00:27:54.220
I'd like it to be natural but it's not possible!

00:27:54.540 --> 00:27:56.340
@Pierre Fournier:

00:27:56.740 --> 00:28:01.240
"Could your Youtube channel become important enough to make you abandon the traditional media?"

00:28:01.380 --> 00:28:01.980
So...

00:28:02.220 --> 00:28:09.680
Dear Pierre, you just put your finger on a strategy that we are working on.

00:28:09.700 --> 00:28:12.280
We've been working on this for months.

00:28:12.500 --> 00:28:17.660
The idea is that we need to be able to bypass the official media system, because it stands like a wall!

00:28:18.160 --> 00:28:26.720
Of course, it's not an absolutely smooth wall, there are niches where you're free to talk,

00:28:26.900 --> 00:28:31.720
but for the most part, it's full of traps and ambushes all the time.

00:28:31.920 --> 00:28:36.820
They say: "Come, we'll ask you questions about your program", but in reality they don't ask me anything.

00:28:36.820 --> 00:28:43.900
They just want me to comment on such and such person, and sometimes, someone suddenly appears and asks a question although he was not supposed to.

00:28:43.900 --> 00:28:48.180
In the traditional media, you always feel like you're taking an oral exam. They ask me:

00:28:48.180 --> 00:28:52.880
"Do you know how many legs a centipede has?", so I say "Yes, yes, a hundred",

00:28:52.880 --> 00:28:58.780
"No! It's 785! You want to be President of the Republic and you don't even know that?!"

00:28:58.780 --> 00:29:04.800
Well no, I didn't! You always feel like you're taking an oral exam in a prestigious university. It allows a caste to reproduce itself

00:29:04.800 --> 00:29:08.200
because you end up thinking: "Well I'm not like them, I don't know everything".

00:29:08.200 --> 00:29:11.260
But they do not know everything, they just learned their notes, that's all!

00:29:11.260 --> 00:29:14.640
In this manner, they create a void around them, and no one dares to do anything!

00:29:14.640 --> 00:29:20.420
So you see people with incredible jobs that require skills and knowledge

00:29:20.420 --> 00:29:24.720
who feel ashamed and confused, but who makes them feel like that?

00:29:24.720 --> 00:29:28.400
Just a bunch of showmen who ask the same questions to everyone!

00:29:28.920 --> 00:29:31.960
Anyway, I'm not going to criticize the media system right now.

00:29:31.960 --> 00:29:37.860
The media system is above all a machine that crushes human beings, journalists in particular,

00:29:38.120 --> 00:29:43.220
who are poorly paid and whose contracts are temporary and uneven.

00:29:43.420 --> 00:29:48.520
It is also a machine that puts people in a box.

00:29:48.940 --> 00:29:54.660
By the way, you should notice that they ask the same questions to everyone, so the system manufactures the public opinion.

00:29:54.740 --> 00:29:57.920
It is so true that when I attend meetings, some people tell me:

00:29:57.920 --> 00:30:01.540
"So some people will ask you questions", and what are these questions?

00:30:01.540 --> 00:30:04.940
The same questions that the journalists ask me! So I end up thinking it's not worth it,

00:30:04.940 --> 00:30:07.220
if I have to answer these questions, I'd better do it on TV.

00:30:07.220 --> 00:30:10.460
So the idea is to bypass the system, but that's easy to say.

00:30:10.460 --> 00:30:14.440
Some people were categorical and told me "Don't go to TV or radio shows, period!"

00:30:14.760 --> 00:30:17.240
I understand this, but then what?

00:30:17.240 --> 00:30:21.340
Do I have to put a bag on my face to look like it's not me? Should I shut up and be invisible?

00:30:21.340 --> 00:30:26.280
Let's be serious! I have to join the fray!

00:30:26.280 --> 00:30:29.640
But I must select the shows I go to, I don't want to be treated like an object.

00:30:29.640 --> 00:30:32.920
That's what the system wants, to turn you into an object.

00:30:32.920 --> 00:30:38.980
It creates a buzz, it puts you in a box... I know what they expect me to say, so I play with their expectations.

00:30:38.980 --> 00:30:45.080
I do this to draw a bit of the public attention , but I need to bypass the system.

00:30:45.080 --> 00:30:47.540
So we created a good system.

00:30:48.280 --> 00:30:54.760
I think it is quite efficient, because something like 541,000 people subscribed to my Facebook page.

00:30:55.180 --> 00:30:59.060
541,000 people, it's like a show with a good audience.

00:30:59.060 --> 00:31:02.060
Almost 900,000 people follow me on Twitter.

00:31:02.060 --> 00:31:07.940
It would have been a dream for me back when I was a young political activist who just handed out his damn tracts on the street.

00:31:07.940 --> 00:31:12.240
You just type 140 characters and poof! 900,000 people get it!

00:31:12.620 --> 00:31:16.260
And there's this Youtube channel of course!

00:31:16.260 --> 00:31:19.300
It made a sudden breakthrough since we are now 70,000 subscribers.

00:31:19.300 --> 00:31:23.400
We're also the leading political channel in  France.

00:31:23.680 --> 00:31:29.560
Of course, some Youtubers have a thousand time more subscribers than I have, but they're in their own domain.

00:31:29.640 --> 00:31:33.860
I'm in politics, people aren't crazy about that!

00:31:34.140 --> 00:31:38.080
The number of subscribers is going to grow as the election is drawing near,

00:31:38.080 --> 00:31:42.500
but you're right Pierre, it's a way of bypassing the system.

00:31:42.500 --> 00:31:46.280
