00:37:30.300 --> 00:37:31.820
@Florent Rué:

00:37:31.820 --> 00:37:36.840
"Don't you think shareholders will back off if their voting rights are modulated according to the duration of their investments in a company?"

00:37:36.960 --> 00:37:37.780
No it won't!

00:37:37.780 --> 00:37:39.220
But first, you need to understand.

00:37:39.220 --> 00:37:47.440
I propose that shareholders' voting rights be proportionate to the duration of their investment,

00:37:47.440 --> 00:37:49.880
which means that someone who says "Well I'll invest money"

00:37:49.880 --> 00:37:51.660
"For how long, Sir?"

00:37:51.660 --> 00:37:52.800
"It's none of your business!"

00:37:52.800 --> 00:37:56.420
"Yes it is, because if you take your money back, my company will go out of business!"

00:37:56.880 --> 00:38:00.740
So to me, shareholders should say how long they want to invest their money.

00:38:00.900 --> 00:38:03.820
For instance, if you don't want to say how long - it's your right -

00:38:03.820 --> 00:38:09.720
if you don't want to say how long you want to invest, then you won't have any voting right as a shareholder.

00:38:09.940 --> 00:38:13.960
If you want to choose the minimum investment period, let's say 3 years, or 5,

00:38:13.960 --> 00:38:17.380
then you will get half a voting right per share,

00:38:17.380 --> 00:38:20.920
and if it's 10 years, then you will get a full voting right per action.

00:38:21.200 --> 00:38:24.580
But you might argue that it's not an anti-capitalist measure.

00:38:24.580 --> 00:38:27.780
Well I'm talking about listed companies here.

00:38:28.220 --> 00:38:32.040
Did you get the point? This measure aims at preventing vampires to hit the road with the funds of a company.

00:38:32.040 --> 00:38:35.700
Those who do that are called "vulture funds", that's their specialty. I'll tell you how they do that.

00:38:35.700 --> 00:38:40.300
They contract a loan from a bank... You always find money when you play these dirty tricks!

00:38:40.300 --> 00:38:41.320
Thank you bankers!

00:38:41.320 --> 00:38:50.420
So they buy a company, and once they own it, they suck out all the company's funds to pay back their loan.

00:38:50.760 --> 00:38:55.000
Sometimes they keep the company working a bit to get some surplus value.

00:38:55.240 --> 00:38:57.140
So they pay back their loan, and then they sell all the rest:

00:38:57.140 --> 00:39:01.420
patents, the order book, even the building sometimes - the walls, the floor, everything!

00:39:01.660 --> 00:39:05.740
You might not be aware of it because you're not used to this kind of things,

00:39:06.020 --> 00:39:11.980
but there was a company that was part of a larger former company, a chemical company,

00:39:12.200 --> 00:39:14.820
I think the name was "Kem One".

00:39:15.120 --> 00:39:17.880
They made PVC. They really were great guys!

00:39:17.900 --> 00:39:20.360
PVC is used to make gutters, things like that...

00:39:20.360 --> 00:39:23.520
It was the only company that did that in France! There were 3 factories!

00:39:24.300 --> 00:39:28.180
A guy bought it for 1€! Can you believe that?

00:39:28.520 --> 00:39:29.140
1€!

00:39:29.220 --> 00:39:32.780
There were 2,900 employees and 3 factories, and do you know what the guy did?

00:39:32.780 --> 00:39:35.280
He thought a 10% benefit was not enough,

00:39:35.780 --> 00:39:38.800
so he sold it all! Everything!

00:39:39.100 --> 00:39:42.940
We have to prevent shareholders who buy a company from selling it, they production  tools,

00:39:42.940 --> 00:39:45.660
and by this I don't mean business and all these liberal tall tales,

00:39:45.660 --> 00:39:50.900
I mean machines and workers, people who have skills.

00:39:52.020 --> 00:39:54.980
So will that deter people from investing? Well no, on the contrary!

00:39:55.120 --> 00:39:59.640
Suppose you have a few savings. You want to invest it in a company that does well,

00:39:59.920 --> 00:40:02.840
not a company that will make you say: "What?

00:40:03.060 --> 00:40:06.080
A hedge fund bought shares in this company? I want to get out of this thing!"

00:40:06.300 --> 00:40:10.880
Because the hedge fund or the pension fund can hit the road whenever it wants,

00:40:10.880 --> 00:40:14.240
and you'll lose all your savings because the company will go bankrupt.

00:40:14.460 --> 00:40:18.780
So on the contrary, we will give stability to investors.

00:40:19.040 --> 00:40:23.320
Now, listen! If you have doubts about this, let me give you another argument.

00:40:24.600 --> 00:40:27.900
There was a time when business was going well in Brazil

00:40:27.900 --> 00:40:30.120
- it's no longer the case right now - but it did.

00:40:30.120 --> 00:40:34.040
There was private money all over the place, in every company,

00:40:35.620 --> 00:40:37.000
and what did Brazilians do?

00:40:37.080 --> 00:40:41.160
They asked for term deposits. They said: "Brazil is not a station hall,

00:40:41.400 --> 00:40:44.860
so if you want to invest, you have to leave a term deposit,

00:40:45.040 --> 00:40:49.820
and if you want to leave in less than 3 years, you can, but we'll keep the deposit.

00:40:50.160 --> 00:40:54.800
And this was not a joke! There were deposits of 10 or 20%

00:40:54.800 --> 00:40:57.700
the total investment, these were susbstantial deposits!

00:40:57.940 --> 00:41:03.300
You see? And it did not prevent business from going well.

00:41:03.300 --> 00:41:07.620
What really matters is the order book, because if it is full,

00:41:07.620 --> 00:41:11.660
